</span></span><span style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:"Arial Unicode MS","sans-serif";
color:black'>Oil from halophytes such as Salicornia bigelovii, which can be
grown using saltwater in coastal areas where conventional crops cannot be
grown, with yields equal to the yields of soybeans and other oilseeds grown
using freshwater irrigation;</span></p>



